# Files and folders not sent to the Docker build context.
#
# Without this, every `docker build` ships the entire repo to the
# daemon — including target/ (multi-GB) and node_modules/. The
# build then runs slower than it should and the image layers can
# inadvertently capture stuff that should not ship.

# Rust build artefacts — always rebuilt inside the image
target/
**/target/

# Node modules — irrelevant for backend Dockerfiles, and web's
# own Dockerfile installs them inside its own build.
node_modules/
**/node_modules/

# Next.js build output
.next/
web/.next/

# Git metadata — large and useless inside an image
.git/
.gitignore
.github/

# Local env files — secrets must never end up in an image layer
.env
.env.local
.env.*.local

# IDE / OS clutter
.vscode/
.idea/
.DS_Store
*.swp

# Test / coverage / cache
*.profraw
.coverage/
coverage/

# Documentation that doesn't need to ship to the build
*.md
!crates/persistence/migrations/README.md